type.name: org.gradle.tooling.model.idea.IdeaModule
type.description:
Represents information about the IDEA module.
(since 1.0-milestone-5)

method.name: getCompilerOutput
method.description:
Returns information about idea compiler output (output dirs, inheritance of output dir, etc.)
(since 1.0-milestone-5)

method.name: getContentRoots
method.description:
All content roots. Most idea modules have a single content root.

returns:content roots
(since 1.0-milestone-5)

method.name: getDependencies
method.description:
dependencies of this module (i.e. module dependencies, library dependencies, etc.)

returns:dependencies
(since 1.0-milestone-5)

method.name: getGradleProject
method.description:
The gradle project that is associated with this module. Typically, a single module corresponds to a single gradle project.

See HasGradleProject

returns:associated gradle project
(since 1.0-milestone-5)

method.name: getIdentifier
method.description:
The unique identifier for this IDEA module.

returns:The unique identifier for this IDEA module.
(since 2.14)

method.name: getJavaLanguageSettings
method.description:
Returns the Java language settings for this element, or null if this element is not a Java element.

returns:The Java language settings. @throws UnsupportedMethodException For Gradle versions older than 2.11, where this method is not supported.
(since 2.11)

method.name: getParent
method.description:
Returns the project of this module. Alias to #getProject()

returns:idea project
(since 1.0-milestone-5)

method.name: getProject
method.description:
Returns the project of this module. Alias to #getParent()

returns:idea project
